# H: Drive Only — Non-Negotiable

**NOTHING is written to C: drive. Everything goes to H: drive.**

## Enforced Paths

| Resource | Path |
|----------|------|
| Project root | `H:\FoundryOS` |
| Node modules | `H:\FoundryOS\node_modules` |
| npm cache | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\npm` |
| Temp files | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\temp` |
| Build output | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\build` |
| Supabase local | `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\supabase` |

## Before Any Install or Build

1. Verify `H:\FoundryOS` is the working directory
2. Confirm `.npmrc` sets cache to `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\npm`
3. Set `TMP` and `TEMP` to `H:\FoundryOS\.cache\temp`
4. Never use `C:\Users\...\AppData` for project artifacts

## Violation Response

If a command attempts to write to C:, **stop immediately**, redirect to H:, and document the fix in `docs/PROTOCOLS.md`.
